'''Glossarium Eroticum''' is a Latin-language dictionary of sexual words and phrases, and of many pertaining to the human body or considered to be obscene, by Pierre-Emmanuel Pierrugues, published in 1826. It lists definitions and excerpts Classical Latin writers such as [[Plautus]], [[Juvenal]], [[Petronius]], and [[Seneca the Younger|Seneca]] in examples, and includes some Medieval Latin as well. 

