{{Infobox museum | name = Zayed National Museum | native_name = <big>'''متحف زايد الوطني'''</big> | image = | caption = | alt = | map_type = | map_caption = | map_alt = | latitude = | longitude = | coordinates = {{coord|24|32|4.43|N|54|25|7.69|E|source:nlwiki_scale:3125_type:landmark}} | established = <!-- {{Start date|2016}} --> | dissolved = | location = [[Saadiyat Island]], [[Abu Dhabi]], [[UAE]] | type = National museum | collection = | visitors = | architect = [[Foster + Partners]] | director = | president = | curator = | publictransit = | network = | website = {{URL|http://www.saadiyat.ae/en/inspiration-details/6/Zayed-National-Museum|Zayed National Museum}} }}
'''Zayed National Museum''' ([[Arabic language|Arabic]]: متحف زايد الوطني) is a planned museum, to be located in [[Abu Dhabi]], [[UAE]]. It is designed as a memorial to the late [[Zayed bin Sultan Al Nahyan]], the founding president of the UAE.<ref name=architect /> The museum is planned to be the centrepiece of the [[Saadiyat Island#Saadiyat Cultural District|Saadiyat Island Cultural District]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.constructionweekonline.com/article-21199-tdic-floats-zayed-national-museum-tender/|title=TDIC floats Zayed National Museum tender {{!}} ConstructionWeekOnline.com|last=Zendera|first=Yamurai|website=www.constructionweekonline.com|access-date=2017-11-08}}</ref> and will showcase the history, culture, and economic transformation of the Emirates.<ref name=earchitect>{{Cite news|url=https://www.e-architect.co.uk/dubai/zayed-national-museum|title=Zayed National Museum, Abu Dhabi Building - e-architect|date=2010-11-25|work=e-architect|access-date=2017-11-08|language=en-GB}}</ref>
The museum has been designed by [[Foster + Partners]] with five solar thermal towers that will act as chimneys to draw cool air through the building.<ref name=architect>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fosterandpartners.com/projects/zayed-national-museum/|title=Zayed National Museum {{!}} Foster + Partners|last=www.fosterandpartners.com|first=Foster + Partners /|website=www.fosterandpartners.com|language=en|access-date=2017-11-08}}</ref> The towers are shaped like falcon wings to commemorate Zayed's love of [[falconry]].<ref name=earchitect />
In 2009, the Zayed Museum signed a ten-year contract with the [[British Museum]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eturbonews.com/10585/british-museum-help-launch-zayed-national-museum-abu-dhabi|title=British Museum to help launch Zayed National Museum in Abu Dhabi|date=July 25, 2009|publisher=eTurboNews|accessdate=October 24, 2011}}</ref><ref name=":0" /> The British Museum would assist with curation and loan about 500 of its treasures to the Zayed Museum.<ref name=":0" />
The museum was projected for completion in 2016, however, as of November 2017, construction has not yet begun.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/30/arts/design/british-museum-abu-dhabi-zayed-national-museum.html|title=Construction Delays Sink British Museum’s Deal With Abu Dhabi|date=October 30, 2017|publisher=NYT|accessdate=November 8, 2017}}</ref> According to ''[[The New York Times]]'', the British Museum thinks that it is unlikely that any items will be loaned under the current contract, which ends in 2019.<ref name=":0" />
